0
appends to the value of 1X* the constant list "1(LIST Y Z)*".
Because the 1QUOTE* construction is used so frequently in LISP,
we use an abbreviated notation: "1'FOO*"
("1FOO*" with a preceding quote-mark)
is equivalent to "1(QUOTE FOO)*".
This is only a notational convenience; the two notations denote
the same list.
